{"abstract":[{"text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Authentication-Flow","text":"Authentication Flow"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":", which contained the "},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here are the changes being made:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters: now, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is responsible."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","type":"reference"},{"text":" is no longer stored inside of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":": now, a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry","type":"reference"},{"text":" holds all instances of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"struct","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"UUID","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" now closely follows "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":", but have moved to default implementations of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A new ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"SessionConfiguration","text":"`SessionConfiguration`"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned previously, ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Furthermore, the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"},{"text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication by waiting on ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"text":" after the server requests a code. Pass the code back through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/receiveCodeFromUser(_:)"},{"text":". The same ","type":"text"},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"-related properties, named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"text":", can also support custom OAuth flows.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned earlier, a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires."}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference"},{"text":" conforms to ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference"},{"text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange"},"sections":[],"kind":"article","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration"},"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/AppleSecureKeychain":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AppleSecureKeychain","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"AppleSecureKeychain","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/applesecurekeychain","fragments":[{"text":"actor","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AppleSecureKeychain","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages the keychains asociated with the sessions for the AT Protocol."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","kind":"symbol"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SessionConfiguration":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SessionConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/sessionconfiguration","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Defines the requirements for session configurations within ATProtoKit."}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"SessionConfiguration","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SessionConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SessionConfiguration/receiveCodeFromUser(_:)":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Takes the Two-Factor Authentication code inputted from the user.","type":"text"}],"required":true,"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"receiveCodeFromUser"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"defaultImplementations":1,"title":"receiveCodeFromUser(_:)","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/sessionconfiguration\/receivecodefromuser(_:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/receiveCodeFromUser(_:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/deleteSession()":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"deleteSession"},{"kind":"text","text":"() "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"async"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","title":"deleteSession()","kind":"symbol"